  "text": "[4] We obtain ground-truth wave fields of velocity and pressure response, p(x, t), by solving the governing equation of acoustic wave propagation in 3-D heterogeneous media using a numerical pseudospectral method [CITATION_1] ]. The simulated pressure pulse excited by an explosive point source situated at one near corner grid of the medium has a Gaussian time duration with a dominant period of t = 25 s, equivalent to the characteristic wavelength of l = 200 km ( Figure 1 ). The synthetic pressure seismograms for travel time measurements are computed at a number of receivers r with different azimuths and straight-line distances L from the source s, ranging from 2.5l to 30l. See Figure A1 in the auxiliary materials 1 for the configuration of source-receiver geometry.",
